  m_text: 'To treat the water, a combination of the following chemicals is usually
    used: Trisodium phosphate, sodium hydroxide, sodium carbonate, and sodium metasilicate.
    These chemicals help prevent scale formation, remove grease and oil, and precipitate
    hardness-causing salts. The water level is monitored using the water level indicator.
    Feed the water until the water level indicator shows 50 percent of the boiler
    filled. Then click next to move on to the next task . '
